sql:
SELECT m.model_name, m.model_owner, mo.output_name, mo.data_type
FROM models m
INNER JOIN model_outputs mo ON m.model_id = mo.model_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'beacon of truth' metaphorically refers to the model's accuracy;
- 'chosen model' refers to the model with model_id 0;
- 'guardian of rules' symbolizes the 'compliance officer';
- 'secluded email address' means the email of the user;
- 'holds the key to this model' implies the user's name (user_name) matches the model's identifier (model_id) in the database.

sql:
SELECT input_name, data_type, description, input_source, input_required, input_default_value
FROM model_inputs
WHERE model_id = 1;
